Quote:  DI: ... I just said, she's different to the usual run-of-the-mill dogshit, that's all.  <i>Ibid.</i> 42 DI: ... Someone told her [the new inmate] I could score, so I helped her out. ... MA: Bit risky, weren't it?  DI: Nah, she's clean. You know how I feel about dogshit.  <i>Ibid.</i>  51  HELEN: ... Tell me something, Ma, what's dogshit?  MA: It's a name the Boss uses.  HELEN: Yeah. What's it mean?  MA: Junkie.  HELEN: So? I'm not the only one in for using. <i>Ibid.</i>  109  Dogshit: an abusive term, used by Di to mean middle-class, well-meaning educated junkies.
